Albaraka Banking, Saudi Fransi: Persian Gulf Equity Preview

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-08-17T02:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-17/albaraka-banking-saudi-fransi-persian-gulf-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in Persian Gulf markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and prices are from the last close.  Saudi Arabia’s  Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX)  fell 1.3 percent,
the most since Aug. 6, to 6,053.73. Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI) 
slid 0.3 percent and  Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  dropped 0.6
percent.  Albaraka Banking Group (BARKA)  BSC: The Turkish unit of
Bahrain’s biggest publicly traded Islamic lender, Albaraka Turk
Katilim Bankasi AS, completed an accord to raise about $340
million from a syndicated Murabahah facility this quarter. The
shares were unchanged at $1.15.  Banque Saudi Fransi (BSFR)  : The Saudi Arabian lender
part-owned by Credit Agricole SA said managing director Jean Marion will resign on Sept. 17 when his term ends. The bank
didn’t name a replacement. The shares declined 0.5 percent to 42
riyals.  Saudi Hollandi Bank (AAAL)  : The Saudi Arabian lender’s
share-price estimate was lowered to 36.43 riyals at Beltone
Financial Holding. The shares rose 3.8 percent to 27.7 riyals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
